Gov . 
  Jerry Brown ordered state officials to impose mandatory water restrictions for the first time in history on Wednesday . 
  Brown said that he had signed an executive order requiring the State Water Resources Control Board to cut water usage by 25 percent compared with 2013 levels . 
  California has been in a drought for four years . 
  State water officials found no snow on the ground at the site for their manual survey of the snowpack . 
  'We're in a historic drought and that demands unprecedented action,' Brown said . 
 